{
  "texts": [
    "In developing these technological implementations, we aimed to keep the infrastructure both open (i.e.",
    "open source, and so consistent with open science practices) and lightweight, so as to make it as easy as possible for anybody to set up their own repository, adapt the Shiny app or R package, or develop additional tooling.",
    "We aimed to make these implementations practically useful to as many researchers as possible (regardless of their philosophical (of science), theoretical, or methodological perspective).",
    "Related, we designed them to be easy (and free or cheap) to create, share, and update.",
    "Furthermore, we designed the technical implementation of DCTs with open standards to facilitate findability, accessibility, interoperability, and re-usability."
  ]
}